@startuml
title Session Lifecycle and Recovery
hide footbox
autonumber

skinparam BackgroundColor transparent
skinparam SequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam ParticipantPadding 20
skinparam BoxPadding 10
skinparam MaxMessageSize 110
skinparam WrapWidth 220
skinparam RoundCorner 8

actor "Host browser\nhost-landing.js" as Host
participant "Daemon session router\n/api/session/*" as SessionAPI
collections "Pending request\nsession.pending" as Pending
participant "Daemon main loop\n__main__.py" as Loop
database "Sessions root\nglobal-state.json" as GlobalState
database "Active session folder\nsession-state.json" as SessionState
participant "Railway daemon WS\nfeatures/ws/router.py" as RailwayWS
participant "Existing host / participant\nsession WS clients" as Clients

Host -> SessionAPI: GET /api/session/active
SessionAPI -> Loop: read shared active session_id
Loop --> SessionAPI: active id or null
SessionAPI --> Host: {session_id|null}

Host -> SessionAPI: GET /api/session/folders
SessionAPI --> Host: current-year session folders

alt Start a brand new session
  Host -> SessionAPI: POST /api/session/create {name, type}
  SessionAPI -> Pending: put(session_request=create)
  SessionAPI --> Host: return generated session_id
else Resume an existing folder
  Host -> SessionAPI: POST /api/session/resume {folder}
  SessionAPI -> SessionState: load stable session_id from selected folder's\nsession-state.json
  SessionAPI -> Pending: put(session_request=create with existing session_id)
  SessionAPI --> Host: return stable session_id
end

Loop -> Pending: pop(session_request)
Loop -> SessionState: create/find active session folder\npersist session_id metadata into session-state.json
Loop -> SessionState: load existing session snapshot or seed a new\nsession-state.json
Loop -> GlobalState: persist global-state.json at sessions root
Loop -> RailwayWS: send set_session_id {session_id, session_name}
RailwayWS -> Clients: redirect + close stale sockets\nwhen the active session changed

note over Loop, GlobalState
The main loop keeps writing the daemon lock heartbeat and
periodically flushes both backups while a session stays active.
end note

== Backend or daemon recovery ==

Loop -> GlobalState: load global-state.json from sessions root at startup
Loop -> SessionState: load session-state.json from the active session folder
Loop -> Loop: restore in-memory session caches from disk
Loop -> RailwayWS: on_connect -> resend set_session_id
RailwayWS -> Clients: allow reconnects for the restored session_id

note over RailwayWS, Clients
Current recovery no longer replays the old monolithic session_sync payload.
Clients reconnect, then fetch fresh state from the daemon-owned REST endpoints.
end note

== End the current session ==

Host -> SessionAPI: POST /api/session/end
SessionAPI -> Pending: put(session_request=end)
Loop -> Pending: pop(end)
Loop -> SessionState: force-flush runtime snapshot to session-state.json
note right of SessionState
Summary and key-point files such as transcript_discussion.md
and ai-summary.md are persisted separately in the session folder.
end note
Loop -> GlobalState: persist global-state.json with empty active_session_id
Loop -> RailwayWS: send set_session_id with no session_id
RailwayWS -> Clients: redirect host to /host\nredirect participants to /?code=<old>&retry=1
@enduml
